    "text": "こう水希はなんかこう何て言うんだろう?"
  },
  {
    "id": 48,
    "text": "ま、学生が進路とかま、まもなくプロセカも5周年を迎えますけど、"
  },
  {
    "id": 49,
    "text": "5周年に向けて色々あった水希ですけど、その中で前を向けたり、"
  },
  {
    "id": 50,
    "text": "前を向くのにはこういうことがあって、"
  },
  {
    "id": 51,
    "text": "でも私は頑張ろうみたいな、私は僕は頑張ろうっていう気持ちをなんか総評して、"
  },
  {
    "id": 52,
    "text": "なんか25の気持ちみたいな感じの飾ってになってると思うんですけど、"
  },
  {
    "id": 53,
    "text": "大沼さんの方は何て言うんだろう?"
  },
  {
    "id": 54,
    "text": "社会人で疲れてる子ががんば、それでも頑張って前を向いて行こうって自分を鼓舞してるみたいなMVになってて、"
  },
  {
    "id": 55,
    "text": "私はなんか歌詞は歌詞でも歌い手とか歌ってる側とか表現の仕方によって曲自体のその幅がすごい広い楽曲なだな飾ってって思ったので、"
  },
  {
    "id": 56,
    "text": "是非ね、あの、大沼さんの方のあの、通じDって言うんだろうか、"
  },
  {
    "id": 57,
    "text": "あれは、何て言うんだろう?"
  },
  {
    "id": 58,
    "text": "MVというんですかね?"
  },
  {
    "id": 59,
    "text": "MVも合わせて楽しんでいただけたらいいなと私は思いました。"
  },
  {
    "id": 60,
    "text": "ま、改めてね、Eベストで言うと、なんか結構これまで2位を全体的になんかこう重ためというかこう息がしにくい部分が露呈する、"
  },
  {
    "id": 61,
    "text": "露見するあの、ストーリーが多かったと思うんですけど一番なんかこう高校2年生だったりとかが、"
  },
  {
    "id": 62,
    "text": "ま、高校1年生からもそうだしま、3年生、"
  },
  {
    "id": 63,
    "text": "高校生が等身大で共感ができるストーリーになっているのではないかなと私は思うイベントストーリーになっているので是非、"
  },
  {
    "id": 64,
    "text": "あの進路の決め方とかうーん、自分の好きを認めてあげることに自信がなかったりとか自分の好きなものを愛してあげられないんだ今はっていう子がもしいたらそれは学生だけじゃなくて社会人の方はもちろんですけど、"
  },
  {
    "id": 65,
    "text": "是非イベントストーリーまだ見れていない方だとだったり楽曲に触れられていない方がいたら、"
  },
  {
    "id": 66,
    "text": "何かね、もしかしたら心に残る言葉みたいなものは今の自分だからこそあるストーリーと楽曲になっていると思うので、"
  },
  {
    "id": 67,
    "text": "是非、あの、大人の皆さんも学生の皆さんも最後まで余すところなく楽しんでいただけたらいいなと私は思います。"
  },
  {
    "id": 68,
    "text": "はい、ということでね、え、イベント届けぬ明日に手を伸ばしてのストーリーをまだ見終わってないという方は次のイベントが始まったらストーリーのイベントストーリーから全て読むことができますのでぜひ読んでください。"
  },
  {
    "id": 69,
    "text": "後日ね、多分YouTubeの方にも、え、アップされると思いますので、"
  },
  {
    "id": 70,
    "text": "そちらを待っていただいても全然大丈夫です。"
  },
  {
    "id": 71,
    "text": "え、アフタートークでは今後もお便りを募集しております。"
  },
  {
    "id": 72,
    "text": "え、プロセカ公式Discordのの募集のチャンネルからアフタートークおたより募集、"
  },
  {
    "id": 73,
    "text": "もしくはメールにて募集を受け付けております。"
  },
  {
    "id": 74,
    "text": "次回のアフタートークのイベントが開始されましたら是非お送りください。"
  },
  {
    "id": 75,
    "text": "え、おたよりはイベントに関する内容でよろしくお願いします。"
  },
  {
    "id": 76,
    "text": "ま、もうもうちょっとで8月も終わりますけど、9月になって9月が終わったら感謝祭が待っております。"
  },
  {
    "id": 77,
    "text": "我々結構ね、あの、ちょこちょこ準備をしておりますので、"
  },
  {
    "id": 78,
    "text": "え、是非是非そっちも楽しみにしてていただけたら嬉しいですし、"
  },
  {
    "id": 79,
    "text": "もう8月も終わっちゃうけど、"
  }
]

response_parts.content:
{
  "response": [
    {
      "id": 0,
      "translated": "[CORNER: Song Watchalong] Now then, let's take a look at the 3DMV right away."
    },
    {
      "id": 1,
      "translated": "Here it is."
    },
    {
      "id": 2,
      "translated": "Did you see that expression just now?"
    },
    {
      "id": 3,
      "translated": "They were smiling."
    },
    {
      "id": 4,
      "translated": "It's so good."
    },
    {
      "id": 5,
      "translated": "Wow, that was wonderful."
    },
    {
      "id": 6,
      "translated": "Honestly, I was blown away when I first saw the MV for \"Consilium.\""
    },
    {
      "id": 7,
      "translated": "I was like, \"I can't believe the scenery changes this much!\""
    },
    {
      "id": 8,
      "translated": "Like, it goes from a school-like setting to an after-school vibe, with shots through windows showing leaves..."
    },
    {
      "id": 9,
      "translated": "And when they're walking down the hallway, you see those little things floating in the light."
    },
    {
      "id": 10,
      "translated": "No, it's not Wi-Fi signals."
    },
    {
      "id": 11,
      "translated": "What would you call it?"
    },
    {
      "id": 12,
      "translated": "Like, not exactly dust, but you can see little particles in the air."
    },
    {
      "id": 13,
      "translated": "The direction is so detailed, I kept wondering how they even did that."
    },
    {
      "id": 14,
      "translated": "It was really, really amazing."
    },
    {
      "id": 15,
      "translated": "And the way everyone spins around and the characters swap out... the direction was just incredible."
    },
    {
      "id": 16,
      "translated": "I loved it."
    },
    {
      "id": 17,
      "translated": "It's great that we can look back at it like this."
    },
    {
      "id": 18,
      "translated": "It's so good, and the 2DMV is also fantastic, so I want you all to see that too."
    },
    {
      "id": 19,
      "translated": "Regarding the 2DMV..."
    },
    {
      "id": 20,
      "translated": "Well, this is just my personal take,"
    },
    {
      "id": 21,
      "translated": "and since it hasn't been officially stated, I'm not entirely sure, but..."
    },
    {
      "id": 22,
      "translated": "In the 2DMV, Mizuki is sitting at a table with a cake, like a birthday seat,"
    },
    {
      "id": 23,
      "translated": "and the camera pans across things that symbolize Mizuki."
    },
    {
      "id": 24,
      "translated": "You see things like the letter from their sister, clothes,"
    },
    {
      "id": 25,
      "translated": "ribbons, and stuff like that appearing."
    },
    {
      "id": 26,
      "translated": "The 2D version was really lovely too."
    },
    {
      "id": 27,
      "translated": "Both were amazing."
    },
    {
      "id": 28,
      "translated": "I was surprised by how much information was packed in there."
    },
    {
      "id": 29,
      "translated": "Also, about the song... I feel like Mizuki's songs usually have a lot of painful lyrics."
    },
    {
      "id": 30,
      "translated": "I'm not trying to compare it to past songs, but I felt this one had a lot of very positive lyrics."
    },
    {
      "id": 31,
      "translated": "Even so, I still feel like Mizuki hasn't fully opened up yet, and there are still swirling emotions inside."
    },
    {
      "id": 32,
      "translated": "So, I consulted with the director about the nuances, like how much weakness"
    },
    {
      "id": 33,
      "translated": "or strength we should add or subtract. We talked a lot while creating this song."
    },
    {
      "id": 34,
      "translated": "For the parts that sound like a radio broadcast,"
    },
    {
      "id": 35,
      "translated": "we discussed whether to put a lot of emotion into it or try making the voice a bit raspy."
    },
    {
      "id": 36,
      "translated": "We consulted on many of those subtle nuances for this track."
    },
    {
      "id": 37,
      "translated": "I hope you enjoy both the full 2DMV and the 3DMV where Mizuki smiles at you."
    },
    {
      "id": 38,
      "translated": "Both are already uploaded to the official ProSeka YouTube channel,"
    },
    {
      "id": 39,
      "translated": "so please go check them out."
    },
    {
      "id": 40,
      "translated": "Well then, although it was a short time,"
    },
    {
      "id": 41,
      "translated": "this concludes the ProSeka AfterTalk for the \"Reaching Out to an Unending Tomorrow\" edition."
    },
    {
      "id": 42,
      "translated": "To everyone watching the stream, how did you like it?"
    },
    {
      "id": 43,
      "translated": "Let me take a look at the comments for a bit."
    },
    {
      "id": 44,
      "translated": "Hmm."
    },
    {
      "id": 45,
      "translated": "\"The atmosphere of Oonuma Parsley-san's MV and Niigo's 2D version were different, but both were great.\""
    },
    {
      "id": 46,
      "translated": "That's so true."
    },
    {
      "id": 47,
      "translated": "For Mizuki, how should I put it?"
    },
    {
      "id": 48,
      "translated": "Well, students have their career paths, and ProSeka is about to reach its 5th anniversary."
    },
    {
      "id": 49,
      "translated": "Mizuki has been through a lot leading up to the 5th anniversary, but they're looking forward now."
    },
    {
      "id": 50,
      "translated": "It shows that this happened, which allowed them to look forward,"
    },
    {
      "id": 51,
      "translated": "and that feeling of \"I'm going to do my best\" is summarized there."
    },
    {
      "id": 52,
      "translated": "I think the Niigo version feels like it's decorated with those feelings."
    },
    {
      "id": 53,
      "translated": "As for Oonuma-san's version, how should I describe it?"
    },
    {
      "id": 54,
      "translated": "It's like an MV where a tired working adult is encouraging themselves to keep going and look ahead."
    },
    {
      "id": 55,
      "translated": "I felt that \"Consilium\" is a song with a very wide range depending on the singer and how it's expressed."
    },
    {
      "id": 56,
      "translated": "So please, check out Oonuma-san's... would you call it a 2D version?"
    },
    {
      "id": 57,
      "translated": "What would you call that?"
    },
    {
      "id": 58,
      "translated": "The music video?"
    },
    {
      "id": 59,
      "translated": "I hope you enjoy that MV as well."
    },
    {
      "id": 60,
      "translated": "Looking back at the event story, Niigo stories have often been heavy or focused on suffocating situations."
    },
    {
      "id": 61,
      "translated": "But I think this story is one that high schoolers—from first to third years—"
    },
    {
      "id": 62,
      "translated": "can really relate to on a personal level."
    },
    {
      "id": 63,
      "translated": "It's an event story that feels very true to life."
    },
    {
      "id": 64,
      "translated": "Whether it's deciding on a career path, or lacking confidence in your own interests... if there's anyone who feels they can't love what they like right now,"
    },
    {
      "id": 65,
      "translated": "and that goes for working adults too, not just students... if you haven't seen the story or heard the song yet,"
    },
    {
      "id": 66,
      "translated": "I think you'll find words that resonate with you exactly because of who you are right now."
    },
    {
      "id": 67,
      "translated": "So, I hope everyone, both adults and students, enjoys it to the very end."
    },
    {
      "id": 68,
      "translated": "If you haven't finished the story for \"Reaching Out to an Unending Tomorrow,\" you can read it all from the event story archive once the next event starts."
    },
    {
      "id": 69,
      "translated": "It will probably be uploaded to YouTube at a later date as well,"
    },
    {
      "id": 70,
      "translated": "so it's perfectly fine to wait for that."
    },
    {
      "id": 71,
      "translated": "[CORNER: Fan Letter Corner] AfterTalk is always looking for your messages."
    },
    {
      "id": 72,
      "translated": "You can submit them through the AfterTalk submission channel on the official ProSeka Discord,"
    },
    {
      "id": 73,
      "translated": "or via email."
    },
    {
      "id": 74,
      "translated": "Please send them in once the next AfterTalk event begins."
    },
    {
      "id": 75,
      "translated": "We look forward to your messages regarding the event."
    },
    {
      "id": 76,
      "translated": "Well, August is almost over, and once September passes, the Thanksgiving festival awaits."
    },
    {
      "id": 77,
      "translated": "We've been busy making preparations here and there,"
    },
    {
      "id": 78,
      "translated": "so I'd be happy if you look forward to that too."
    },
    {
      "id": 79,
      "translated": "August is ending, but..."
    }
  ]
}
